Package com.example.filemanager.logic.commands.commands

package com.example.filemanager.logic.commands.commands
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    DeleteFilesCommand
    A command that deletes all files from context working[], temporally stores them so that action can be undone.
    DuplicateFileCommand
    A convenient wrapper around PASTE command for pasting from source to source, ie, duplicating in same directory.
    FileCommand
    A command class for logic commands.
    FindCommand
    Searches recursively for file with pattern given with the name of the first file in `working` in context.
    ListAllCommand
    A command to list all files.
    NewDirectoryCommand
    A command to create the first file in context working as directory
    NewFileCommand
    A command to create the first file in context working (working[0])
    OpenFileCommand
    A command to open a file.
    PasteFilesCommand
    A command to paste all files from context working[] into context directory.
    RenameFileCommand
    Renames the first file in `working` in context to the name of the second file there.
